word-sys-pdf-editor (1.8.3) bookworm; urgency=medium

  * Renamed project from Word-Sys's PDF Editor to word-sys's PDF Editor
  * Updated all branding references from word-sys to word-sys
  * Fixed language support (i18n) for About page — comments, website label, and author now respect active language
  * Fixed hardcoded Turkish strings in font combo, shape color dialogs, bold/italic tooltips, and status bar
  * Updated config directory from word-sys-pdf-editor to word-sys-pdf-editor
  * Updated repository URLs to github.com/word-sys/word-sys-pdf-editor
  * Added missing i18n keys: about_comments, about_website_label, font_loading, font_warning, shape dialog titles, transparent label
  * Multi-distro compatibility: package now works on Debian 12 (bookworm),
    Debian 13 (trixie), and Ubuntu 22.04 (Jammy) from a single .deb file
  * Architecture changed from amd64-only to Architecture: all — supports both
    x86_64 and arm64 hosts from the same package
  * Replaced build-time pip vendoring of PyMuPDF/numpy with a postinst script
    that creates a per-host Python venv at /opt/word-sys-pdf-editor/.venv and
    installs the correct binary wheel for the host Python version at install time
  * Added prerm script to cleanly remove the venv on package uninstall
  * Added python3-venv and python3-pip as runtime dependencies
  * Always installs latest PyMuPDF at package-install time via pip (requires-python >= 3.10)

 -- Barın Güzeldemirci <baringuzeldemir@gmail.com>  Thu, 24 Apr 2026 23:24:00 +0300

